from test: 13 The Mg*H sites may combine to produce hydrogen, H2, and making available the two metal sites Mg* (Figure 4). Note at this point that our mechanism has assumed that no charge transfer has yet taken place: it involves the recombination of neutral hydrogen atoms to make neutral H2.
