from test: 27 Having now presented the basis for, and the results of, the derivation of the hydrogen evolution rate, K2, as a function of the fundamental rate constants k1-4, we will now use a first-principles approach to quantify the rate constants, and hence see if the proposed combination of mechanisms can account for the negative difference effect of hydrogen evolution on pure magnesium.
