from Soup: 35 Once again, the phenomenology between Figures 2 (from experimental data) and Figure 9 (the current model) is in considerably good agreement, indicative that the proposed model, grounded in the latest density functional theory studies of fundamental magnesium surface chemical properties, provides a potentially useful model for accounting for the negative difference effect.
