from Soup: 37 At present the estimated rate constants do not allow for precise prediction of the absolute rates of hydrogen evolution or the anodic/cathodic current densities associated with the change in potential. Pre-factors can be more accurately determined from first-principles when certain kinds of accelerated molecular dynamic simulations are employed, for example. 32
