from Soup: 38 An additional area of concern is that the formation of hydroxide films is not taken into account in this model- rather, we assume that the hydroxide films take a longer time scale to form compared to the events that lead to the fast moving corrosion front in magnesium alloys. It might be the case that, even when the system is cathodically polarized, a nanoscale hydroxide film is present on the material, and, as shown recently, this hydroxide film might have considerable activity for HER. 15
